<TITLE> Police force to expand by '32,000 in 3 years' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 4 (bdnews24.com)The government will appoint 32,000 new police personnel over three years, home minister Sahara Khatun said on Sunday. Sahara was speaking at programme organised by the International Women Police Association at Rajarbag police line. She greeted some 193 policewomen who earned membership of the association. The home minister said, "On an average we now have one police officer for 1,200 people. To reduce the huge gap the government has adopted plans to recruit some 32,000 police personnel in the next three years." Women recruitment will be specially be encouraged in the sector, said Sahara. Prime minister Sheikh Hasina at the recent UN General Assembly session in New York had pledged more policewomen in Bangladesh police missions abroad, Sahara added. The minister too hoped for more women participation in foreign missions. The programme was presided over by Fatema Begum, deputy inspector general of police in the Criminal Investigation Department . UNDP representative Renata Lock Dessalien, home secretary Abdus Sobhan Shikdar, chief of Police Reforms Programme (PRP) and additional inspector general of police Naba Bikram Tripura were among the speakers. bdnews
